{"Author": "JD", "Date": "on October 20, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This Samsung SmartThings hub is a good device to manage different devices in your smart home", "Text": "This Samsung SmartThings hub is a good device to manage different devices in your smart home. However, the automation routines still need a lot more works (customization) for the hub to be great device.\n\nFor one thing, the automation routines allow many customization rules to be configured. However, the rules fall short of one very simple logic and that is the duration of the \"on\" state for a device. For example, you can create an automation routine for disarming the alarm and turning on a light when someone arrives between 7PM and 10PM at night, but you cannot configure the light to stay on for a certain amount of time before the routine turns the light off. If I only want the light the be on for 5 minutes when I arrive, I cannot create a routine for this. You can only create a routine for turning things on and turning things off, but you cannot create a routine for turning things on for a certain amount of time. Some people may ask why don't I just create a routing to turn off the light? My answer would be \"yes, I could!\" but since I don't know what time I'll be arriving, I can't create a routine to turn the light off if I don't know what time the time will be turned on.\n\nThere are other simple and logical settings that are totally missing from the configurations. This is not a hard fix, so hopefully someone with a common sense would fix it in the next software update."}
{"Author": "Nick Allen", "Date": "on October 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Best device to turn your home into a smart home!", "Text": "This product has turned my house into a smart home in no time at all. Gives me the ability to control my light switches, outlets, and notifies me when all doors to my house open and close. Easy connectivity and great instructions to setup and get started!"}
{"Author": "Kaleem", "Date": "on October 19, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Simple, affordable, and worth it.", "Text": "Connected this to an Amazon Echo Dot.\nSimple home automation device with a lot of capabilities.\nBought a bunch of LED z-wave/zigbee lights, door locks, switches, sensors, etc and connected them to the HUB.\nI can control the lights around my house, and I can even turn on or off the lights when Im not home. (or dim them).\nI also set timers to have lights come on and off at certain times of the day.\nI even set lights to trigger when my motion sensor detects movement in my hallway.\n\nIt does have a bit of delay from time to time, but mostly reacts almost instantly.\nI can keep an eye on what I left on or off in the house ,while not being at home.\nPresence sensor is a bit sometime-ish (it works with my phone, but it always tells me that my wife is home, even when she isnt...)\nLots of premade templates for setting up Automated scenes.\nYou can even program your own (but requires a bit of research and understanding first...)\nCompatible with many devices (ranging from cheap and simple to complex and pricey)\n\nNote: don't treat this as a Security System but more like a Home Automated System."}
{"Author": "DMS", "Date": "on October 18, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "OK but...", "Text": "Setting up was a nightmare. Range is terrible but now it is finally working. Phone app worked and then died. Reinstall was never able to use the hub but since things are working with Alexa, I gave up tryin to use the phone app."}
{"Author": "Luis Miguel Gon\u00e7alves", "Date": "on October 17, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Worse purchase I ever did at Amazon", "Text": "Worse purchase I ever did at Amazon.\n\nI bought just recently a brand new series 8 Samsung TV, and bought this hub in order to control the TV together with Amazon Alexa.\n\nNot only the installation process was dumb, and spend hours on the phone with the Samsung SmartThings support to get it working as at the end... I had to hear that the Samsung Smarthings hub is not compatible with most of the brand new Samsung TV's as was my case!!!!"}
