{"Author": "Tom", "Date": "on October 11, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Flawless", "Text": "Bravo, Amazon!! I bought this and it would not work. (May have been an error by me!) But, when I printed the return label, I was immediately shipped a new (with two day shipping) prior to my sending it back! ...impressive! The new one arrived and worked perfectly.\nI must say that this hub has worked flawlessly with all my lighting and home automation items I have bought. I have Z-Wave, ZigBee, IHome and Alexa items. SmartThings Hub works perfectly with ALL of them!\nHighly recommended for those of you doing home automation!!"}
{"Author": "Brian Dirrim", "Date": "on October 9, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "This is a good replacement and it was fairly easy to setup my ...", "Text": "had the Staples Connect hub, but since the developer when out of business, I could not use it any longer. This is a good replacement and it was fairly easy to setup my Z-wave devices."}
{"Author": "Neal", "Date": "on October 8, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "A very good product. But not all devices work with all hubs.", "Text": "My first endeavor in Home Automation. Worked right out of the box!"}
{"Author": "Lou Lembcke", "Date": "on October 7, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Stopped working after two weeks", "Text": "My hub worked for about two weeks, both through the mobile app and Amazon Echo, and then stopped working. It shows as offline or inactive in the mobile app, and unavailable to Amazon Echo. I followed the support directions, without joy. I've reset using the recessed reset button, and got a green light, but still showed as offline. I unplugged power & network cables & pulled the batteries, and got a green light, but still shows as offline.\n\nI'll be replacing with a different ZigBee & ZWave hub."}
