{"Author": "A. Olson", "Date": "on October 6, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Four Stars", "Text": "Hub arrived on time and appears to be in good shape."}
{"Author": "TM", "Date": "on October 5, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "the hub seems to operate fine.", "Text": "The hub is relatively simple to install. I\u2019m giving it three stars because it has a hard time connecting with many Z wave devices. Many times the only solution is to Google on the tricks needed to get a particular Z wave device to connect. What\u2019s connected however, the hub seems to operate fine."}
{"Author": "Amz J", "Date": "on October 4, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I really like the device and the app but there are several ...", "Text": "I really like the device and the app but there are several reliability issues.\n1) Samsung leak sensors stop talking to the device and it says \"Everything OK\". It's not OK if you can't get a reading from the sensor.\n2) Becomes unresponsive and you have to open the device and pull the batteries to get it back online. The app doesn't alert you that the hub is offline either which isn't ok.\n3) Some of the automations have just stopped running and the only way to get them to start running again was to go in and re-save them.\nThese have made this experience of using this frustrating and you can't rely on things to work. You shouldn't have to go in every day and check the application logs to make sure it's all working properly."}
{"Author": "Kolinl79", "Date": "on October 3, 2017", "Stars": "2.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "I give up...", "Text": "Why have I given you up? Because I have been working with SmartThings since Hub v1 and to give you an overview, there have been too many ups and downs to keep going with this technology. Even the past 9 months has been sketchy.\n\nBecause you hear complaints first out of these reviews, I will start there first.\n- Connectivity issues: From no notifications, to failed communication to batteries needing to be replaced frequently.\n- Outages: There are quite a few outages that occur, while they don't affect me that from what I know, there are frequent and concerning\n- Samsung purchase: It seems since the Samsung purchase of the company, the software has taken a dive.\n- Product support: It's been slower to non-existent and some features I would expect to see, haven't happened yet.\n\nWhat is the good?\n- My hub works most of the time: This is good, specifically when it comes to safety, Z-wave smoke alarms, etc.\n- Apps/Interface: While not the best, it's pretty good and somewhat easy to use.\n\nIt's unfortunate, good luck to those who want to venture into the unknown. I hope they get their stuff together. I won't replace SmartThings until I can get another Z-Wave hub in place, for now, it's staying here but not for long."}
{"Author": "Tim M.", "Date": "on October 3, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Five Stars", "Text": "We love it! Genius"}
{"Author": "Brian Hauptman", "Date": "on October 2, 2017", "Stars": "4.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Would be better if this worked wirelessly.", "Text": "Wish it would work wirelessly - seems kind of silly to require a wired connection to control wireless devices."}
{"Author": "Asketes", "Date": "on October 2, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Awesome!", "Text": "Love it!\n\nInterface can be a little tricky but overall this is really fantastic. I would love to see this support ZigBee stuff too."}
{"Author": "??_RO7??", "Date": "on October 2, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Unreliable Junk. Buyer beware.", "Text": "This is a buggy and unreliable device. It works some of the time, but other times it can\u2019t communicate with other devices that are only 20 or 30 feet away.\n\nI very much regret buying this, but more than that I regret investing money in Samsung compatible sensors, which are also unreliable junk.\n\nThere are open standards and yet companies like Samsung spend marketing dollars to try to get you locked in to their proprietary version, and so when that version turns out to be buggy and unreliable the cost is far higher than replacing a single device.\n\nNobody should rely on this system for home security or water leak monitoring. It is a toy and not reliable enough to be trusted to prevent property damage.\n\nBuyer beware."}
