{"Author": "Nelson R. Pardee", "Date": "on July 30, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Samsung SmartThings Smart Home Hub - Problematic- fast ST response", "Text": "I really want to like this. Sometimes I even do like it, but...\nI purchased this to replace my v1 hub, but it was terribly frustrating to have to delete all my old devices and then re-pair. That may be a zwave issue, but I wish ST would just say so- \"We can't do it because of zwave constraints.\"\nST would not unpair any of my devices from the old Hub, so I had to exclude each one manually from the v2 hub as well as force an exclude from the v1 hub.\nI have a Linear/Nortek/GoControl fs20z switch. I can exclude it from the v2 hub, but can't pair it. Yeah, I know it's probably not ST's fault, but it did pair with the v1 hub.\nAnd what is not ST's fault- the multitudinous ways of making a device pair, including take the device apart. It should pair- obviously- when installed, and have an internal switch that would disable external pairing for applications where drive-by pairing is undesirable.\nI've been a techie all my life, and this is still too hard.\nUpdate: ST responded immediately to this post."}
{"Author": "Todd A Gondek", "Date": "on July 30, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Great for home automation", "Text": "Love my smartthings hub. I got it for Christmas and it has been great ever since. Love the alerts and notifications. I now know when people arrive and leave my house, if my sump pump has stopped working, and no long need to manually turn on light at night when he arrive home. I pairs great with Alexa and GE smart light switches. The range is excellent because all of my GE z-wave wall switches act as repeaters to extend my z-wave network. When I moved my hub one of my switches would no longer work but I simply z-wave network repair through the app on my iPhone and it fixed the problem immediately. The routines are the best because they trigger automatically without any effort on my part (once set up). I have had it 8 months now and have had very few problems."}
{"Author": "Amazon Customer", "Date": "on July 29, 2017", "Stars": "5.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Samsung Smart Things Hub", "Text": "This is a great Hub for ZigBee and Z Wave users. I started with the Hue Hub and rapidly looked for something with more capabilities and compatible with multiple vendors. The Smart Things Hub fit the bill and am very satisfied with it."}
