{"Author": "Elmo Bagley", "Date": "on July 21, 2017", "Stars": "3.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "works great, setup is a chore.", "Text": "Operationally, this is great for home automation, but setup is really clunky. I have to move the unit within 10 ft of the device I want to add to it, but what if that device is installed in my wall, like a light switch? No worries, just move the hub close to the switch... except the hub itself doesn't have wifi, so I had to build a 50 ft ethernet cable so I could string it all around the house and install my switches and other installed devices. I would dock more stars, because the first unit they sent was faulty. But Amazon support came through, and replaced it without hassle. Also, once it's up, it works great! so 3 stars!"}
