{"Author": "Kevin S", "Date": "on March 19, 2017", "Stars": "1.0 out of 5 stars", "Title": "Amazingly bad. Not for iPhone users", "Text": "\"Upgraded\" from the Wink 1 Hub to this and shocked by how bad the app is compared to Wink. If you are an iPhone user, Groups are a foreign idea to this App although allegedly, you can maybe do this on Android. Why on earth would you want to turn on a group of lights together? It also fails to turn on lights in scheduled routines where my original Wink hub never failed. It will tell you a light is on in a routine that is absolutely not on. It's also way slower than the original Wink hub for turning dimmers on and off. I'm ordering the Wink 2 and putting this upgrade in the trash bin."}
